TITLE: Entire island of Puerto Rico loses power as Hurricane Fiona makes landfall
SUMMARY: Fiona has strengthened to a Category 1 hurricane as is heads toward the U.S. Virgin Islands.

TITLE: Suits to save Confederate icons dropped in South Carolina
SUMMARY: Lawsuits filed to stop the removal of memorials to Confederate leaders and a pro-slavery congressman in a South Carolina city have been dropped

TITLE: EXPLAINER: How the strong U.S. dollar can affect everyone
SUMMARY: The dollar is near its highest level in two decades against a key index.

TITLE: Pelosi condemns Azerbaijan over Armenia attack
SUMMARY: Speaker of the U.S. House of Representatives Nancy Pelosi says the United States deplores recent attacks by Azerbaijan on Armenia, and has called for a negotiated solution to the countries’ conflict

TITLE: Steven Spielberg's 'Fabelmans' wins Toronto audience award
SUMMARY: Steven Spielberg’s autobiographical coming-of-age drama “The Fabelmans” won the Toronto International Film Festival’s top prize, the People’s Choice Award, solidifying its early status as Academy Awards frontrunner

TITLE: Multiple fatalities after 2 small aircraft collide mid-air in Colorado
SUMMARY: Two small aircraft collided over Boulder County Saturday morning, resulting in three confirmed fatalities at this time, authorities said.

TITLE: Iconic Russian singer asks to be named 'foreign agent'
SUMMARY: Iconic Russian singer Alla Pugacheva, hugely popular since Soviet times, says she wants to be placed on Russia’s foreign agents list in solidarity with her husband who has been designated as one

TITLE: Michigan man who wanted to admit to killing gets a new trial
SUMMARY: A Michigan man’s 2019 second-degree murder conviction has been overturned by an appeals court that determined the man’s attorney ignored his wishes to admit that he pulled the trigger

TITLE: Kentucky court suspends prosecutor who asked for nude photos
SUMMARY: The Kentucky Supreme Court has suspended an Eastern Kentucky prosecutor who promised to help a defendant in exchange for nude photos

TITLE: New model to enlist regular Americans to resettle refugees
SUMMARY: With refugee resettlement agencies overwhelmed after being gutted by the Trump administration, thousands of Americans heeded the call to help Afghans restart their lives in far-flung towns across the United States with little to no immigrant populations

TITLE: Mexican faith leader jailed for sex abuse; flock stays loyal
SUMMARY: The leader of a multinational, Mexico-based Christian church is imprisoned in California after pleading guilty to sexually abusing minors

TITLE: EU proposes to suspend billions in funds to Hungary
SUMMARY: The European Union’s executive branch has recommended that the bloc suspend around 7.5 billion euros (dollars) in funding to Hungary

TITLE: 14 people die in iron mine flood in China, 1 missing
SUMMARY: Chinese authorities say 14 people died and one remains missing after a flood at an iron mine earlier this month

TITLE: LIVE:  ABC News Live
SUMMARY: 24/7 coverage of breaking news and live events

TITLE: Strong Taiwan earthquake traps people, derails train
SUMMARY: A strong earthquake has shaken much of Taiwan, killing one person and injuring nine

TITLE: WATCH:  Baby antelope explores Florida zoo enclosure
SUMMARY: A bongo antelope calf playfully explored her enclosure at the Jacksonville Zoo just days after she was born.

SUMMARY: Ilia Malinin, 17, successfully landed the feat, spinning 4 1/2 revolutions in the air, at the U.S. Classic in Lake Placid, New York.

SUMMARY: "We all want to be here together,” Beckham told reporters while waiting to see the queen's coffin at Westminster Hall.

SUMMARY: A photographer and his daughter captured the northern lights dancing over Iceland's capital.

SUMMARY: Angus, the seafaring Alaskan malamute, howls his way across a Norwegian harbor in a canine salute to passing boats.

TITLE: WATCH:  UK man pays tribute to Queen Elizabeth II with tattoo
SUMMARY: An English tattoo parlor said it's been fielding numerous requests regarding tributes to Queen Elizabeth II since her death.
